    public interface IRequestHistory
extends List<IRequestHistoryEntry>
    Used to track the history of operations on a market entity.

    For example, this can be used to track the amendment history of an order. In such an example, the id of the request history would be the ClOrderID and each entry would correspond to an amend or cancel request on that order.

    It is assumed that all requests are acknowledged in some way - either accepted or rejected.

    It is also assumed that each request is associated with a unique ID. The only requests that are not associated with an ID are "fictional" requests that may be inserted as "placeholders" for unsolicited ack's.
